#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:111
msgid "ptool.inspect"
msgstr "ptool.inspect"

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:113
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:113"
msgid "`v0.1.0` - Introduced."
msgstr "`v0.1.0` - Introducido."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:115
msgid "`ptool.inspect(value[, options])` renders a Lua value as a readable Lua-style string. It is primarily intended for debugging and displaying table contents."
msgstr "`ptool.inspect(value[, options])` representa un valor Lua como una cadena legible al estilo Lua. Su objetivo principal es depurar y mostrar el contenido de tablas."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:118
msgid "`value` (any, required): The Lua value to inspect."
msgstr "`value` (any, obligatorio): El valor Lua que se va a inspeccionar."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:119
msgid "`options` (table, optional): Rendering options. Supported fields:"
msgstr "`options` (table, opcional): Opciones de renderizado. Campos admitidos:"

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:119
msgid "`indent` (string, optional): Indentation used for each nesting level. Defaults to two spaces."
msgstr "`indent` (string, opcional): Indentación usada en cada nivel de anidación. Por defecto son dos espacios."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:119
msgid "`multiline` (boolean, optional): Whether tables are rendered across multiple lines. Defaults to `true`."
msgstr "`multiline` (boolean, opcional): Si las tablas se representan en varias líneas. Por defecto es `true`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:119
msgid "`max_depth` (integer, optional): Maximum nesting depth to render. Deeper values are replaced with `<max-depth>`."
msgstr "`max_depth` (integer, opcional): Profundidad máxima de anidación que se representará. Los valores más profundos se reemplazan por `<max-depth>`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:126
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:126"
msgid "Returns: `string`."
msgstr "Devuelve: `string`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:128
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:128"
msgid "Behavior:"
msgstr "Comportamiento:"

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:130
msgid "Array-like entries (`1..n`) are rendered first."
msgstr "Las entradas tipo arreglo (`1..n`) se representan primero."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:131
msgid "Remaining table fields are rendered after the array part in stable key order."
msgstr "Los demás campos de la tabla se representan después de la parte tipo arreglo, con un orden estable por clave."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:132
msgid "Identifier-like string keys are rendered as `key = value`; other keys are rendered as `[key] = value`."
msgstr "Las claves de cadena con forma de identificador se representan como `key = value`; las demás se representan como `[key] = value`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:134
msgid "Recursive table references are rendered as `<cycle>`."
msgstr "Las referencias recursivas a tablas se representan como `<cycle>`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:135
msgid "Functions, threads, and userdata are rendered as placeholder values such as `<function>` and `<userdata>`."
msgstr "Las funciones, threads y userdata se representan con valores marcadores como `<function>` y `<userdata>`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:138
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:138"
msgid "Example:"
msgstr "Ejemplo:"

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:151
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:151"
msgid "ptool.ask"
msgstr "ptool.ask"

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:153
msgid "`v0.1.0` - Introduced. `v0.5.0` - Added prompt validation options and prompt subcommands."
msgstr "`v0.1.0` - Introduced. `v0.5.0` - Added validation options and prompt subcommands."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:156
msgid "`ptool.ask` provides interactive prompts. You can call it directly for text input, or use its prompt subcommands for confirmation, selection, multi-select, and secret input."
msgstr "`ptool.ask` ofrece prompts interactivos. Puedes llamarlo directamente para pedir texto, o usar sus subprompts para confirmación, selección simple, selección múltiple y entrada secreta."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:160
msgid "Common behavior:"
msgstr "Comportamiento común:"

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:162
msgid "All `ptool.ask` prompts require an interactive TTY. Running them in a non-interactive environment raises an error."
msgstr "Todos los prompts de `ptool.ask` requieren un TTY interactivo. Ejecutarlos en un entorno no interactivo produce un error."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:164
msgid "If the user cancels a prompt, the script raises an error."
msgstr "Si el usuario cancela un prompt, el script produce un error."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:165
msgid "Unknown option names or invalid option value types raise an error."
msgstr "Los nombres de opción desconocidos o los tipos de valor no válidos producen un error."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:167
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:167"
msgid "ptool.ask"
msgstr "ptool.ask"

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:169
msgid "`ptool.ask(prompt[, options])` asks the user for a line of text and returns the answer."
msgstr "`ptool.ask(prompt[, options])` pide al usuario una línea de texto y devuelve la respuesta."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:172
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:172"
msgid "`prompt` (string, required): The prompt shown to the user."
msgstr "`prompt` (string, obligatorio): El prompt que se muestra al usuario."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:173
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:173"
msgid "`options` (table, optional): Prompt options. Supported fields:"
msgstr "`options` (table, opcional): Opciones del prompt. Campos admitidos:"

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:173
msgid "`default` (string, optional): Default value used when the user submits an empty answer."
msgstr "`default` (string, opcional): Valor por defecto usado cuando el usuario envía una respuesta vacía."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:173
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:173"
msgid "`help` (string, optional): Extra help text shown below the prompt."
msgstr "`help` (string, opcional): Texto de ayuda adicional mostrado bajo el prompt."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:173
msgid "`placeholder` (string, optional): Placeholder text shown before the user starts typing."
msgstr "`placeholder` (string, opcional): Texto placeholder mostrado antes de que el usuario empiece a escribir."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:173
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:173"
msgid "`required` (boolean, optional): Whether the answer must be non-empty."
msgstr "`required` (boolean, opcional): Si la respuesta debe ser no vacía."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:173
msgid "`allow_empty` (boolean, optional): Whether to accept an empty answer. Defaults to `true`."
msgstr "`allow_empty` (boolean, opcional): Si se acepta una respuesta vacía. El valor por defecto es `true`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:173
msgid "`trim` (boolean, optional): Whether to trim leading and trailing whitespace from the answer before returning it."
msgstr "`trim` (boolean, opcional): Si se deben recortar los espacios al inicio y al final antes de devolver la respuesta."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:173
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:173"
msgid "`min_length` (integer, optional): Minimum accepted character length."
msgstr "`min_length` (integer, opcional): Longitud mínima aceptada."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:173
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:173"
msgid "`max_length` (integer, optional): Maximum accepted character length."
msgstr "`max_length` (integer, opcional): Longitud máxima aceptada."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:173
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:173"
msgid "`pattern` (string, optional): Regular expression the answer must match."
msgstr "`pattern` (string, opcional): Expresión regular que la respuesta debe cumplir."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:187
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:187"
msgid "Returns: `string`."
msgstr "Devuelve: `string`."

