#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:382
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:382"
msgid "Behavior:"
msgstr "Comportamiento:"

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:384
msgid "When running through `ptool run <file>`, this returns the entry script path as an absolute, normalized path."
msgstr "Al ejecutar con `ptool run <file>`, devuelve la ruta del script de entrada como una ruta absoluta y normalizada."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:386
msgid "The returned path is fixed when the runtime starts and does not change after `ptool.cd(...)`."
msgstr "La ruta devuelta queda fijada cuando se inicia el runtime y no cambia después de `ptool.cd(...)`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:388
msgid "In `ptool repl`, this returns `nil`."
msgstr "En `ptool repl`, devuelve `nil`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:390
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:390"
msgid "Example:"
msgstr "Ejemplo:"

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:398
msgid "ptool.try"
msgstr "ptool.try"

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:400
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:400"
msgid "`v0.4.0` - Introduced."
msgstr "`v0.4.0` - Introducido."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:402
msgid "`ptool.try(fn)` runs `fn` and converts raised errors into return values."
msgstr "`ptool.try(fn)` ejecuta `fn` y convierte los errores lanzados en valores de retorno."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:404
msgid "`fn` (function, required): Callback to execute."
msgstr "`fn` (function, obligatorio): Callback que se va a ejecutar."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:405
msgid "Returns: `ok, value, err`."
msgstr "Devuelve: `ok, value, err`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:407
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:407"
msgid "Return value rules:"
msgstr "Reglas del valor devuelto:"

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:409
msgid "On success, `ok = true`, `err = nil`, and `value` contains the callback result."
msgstr "En caso de éxito, `ok = true`, `err = nil` y `value` contiene el resultado del callback."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:411
msgid "If the callback returns no values, `value` is `nil`."
msgstr "Si el callback no devuelve valores, `value` es `nil`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:412
msgid "If the callback returns one value, `value` is that value."
msgstr "Si el callback devuelve un solo valor, `value` es ese valor."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:413
msgid "If the callback returns multiple values, `value` is an array-like table."
msgstr "Si el callback devuelve varios valores, `value` es una tabla tipo arreglo."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:414
msgid "On failure, `ok = false`, `value = nil`, and `err` is a table."
msgstr "En caso de fallo, `ok = false`, `value = nil` y `err` es una tabla."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:416
msgid "Structured error fields:"
msgstr "Campos de error estructurado:"

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:418
msgid "`kind` (string): Stable error category such as `io_error`, `command_failed`, `invalid_argument`, `http_error`, or `lua_error`."
msgstr "`kind` (string): Categoría estable del error, como `io_error`, `command_failed`, `invalid_argument`, `http_error` o `lua_error`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:420
msgid "`message` (string): Human-readable error message."
msgstr "`message` (string): Mensaje de error legible para humanos."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:421
msgid "`op` (string, optional): API or operation name such as `ptool.fs.read`."
msgstr "`op` (string, opcional): Nombre de la API u operación, como `ptool.fs.read`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:422
msgid "`detail` (string, optional): Extra detail for the failure."
msgstr "`detail` (string, opcional): Detalle adicional del fallo."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:423
msgid "`path` (string, optional): Path involved in a filesystem failure."
msgstr "`path` (string, opcional): Ruta implicada en un fallo del sistema de archivos."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:424
msgid "`input` (string, optional): Original input that failed to parse or validate."
msgstr "`input` (string, opcional): Entrada original que no pudo analizarse o validarse."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:425
msgid "`cmd` (string, optional): Command name for command failures."
msgstr "`cmd` (string, opcional): Nombre del comando en fallos de comandos."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:426
msgid "`status` (integer, optional): Exit status or HTTP status when available."
msgstr "`status` (integer, opcional): Código de salida o código HTTP cuando esté disponible."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:427
msgid "`stderr` (string, optional): Captured stderr for command failures."
msgstr "`stderr` (string, opcional): stderr capturado en fallos de comandos."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:428
msgid "`url` (string, optional): URL involved in an HTTP failure."
msgstr "`url` (string, opcional): URL implicada en un fallo HTTP."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:429
msgid "`cwd` (string, optional): Effective working directory for command failures."
msgstr "`cwd` (string, opcional): Directorio de trabajo efectivo en fallos de comandos."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:430
msgid "`target` (string, optional): SSH target for SSH-related command failures."
msgstr "`target` (string, opcional): Objetivo SSH en fallos de comandos relacionados con SSH."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:431
msgid "`retryable` (boolean): Whether retrying may make sense. Defaults to `false`."
msgstr "`retryable` (boolean): Si tiene sentido reintentar. El valor por defecto es `false`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:433
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:433"
msgid "Behavior:"
msgstr "Comportamiento:"

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:435
msgid "`ptool` APIs raise structured errors. `ptool.try` converts them into the `err` table above so callers can branch on `err.kind` and related fields."
msgstr "Las APIs de `ptool` lanzan errores estructurados. `ptool.try` los convierte en la tabla `err` anterior para que quien llama pueda ramificar según `err.kind` y otros campos."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:437
msgid "Plain Lua errors are also caught. In that case, `err.kind` is `lua_error`, and only `message` is guaranteed."
msgstr "Los errores Lua normales también se capturan. En ese caso, `err.kind` es `lua_error` y solo se garantiza `message`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:439
msgid "`ptool.try` is the recommended way to handle errors from APIs such as `ptool.fs.read`, `ptool.http.request`, `ptool.run(..., { check = true })`, and `res:assert_ok()`."
msgstr "`ptool.try` es la forma recomendada de manejar errores de APIs como `ptool.fs.read`, `ptool.http.request`, `ptool.run(..., { check = true })` y `res:assert_ok()`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:443
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:443"
msgid "Example:"
msgstr "Ejemplo:"

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:468
msgid "ptool.run"
msgstr "ptool.run"

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:470
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:470"
msgid "`v0.1.0` - Introduced."
msgstr "`v0.1.0` - Introducido."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:472
msgid "`ptool.run` executes external commands from Rust."
msgstr "`ptool.run` ejecuta comandos externos desde Rust."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:474
msgid "The following call forms are supported:"
msgstr "Se admiten las siguientes formas de llamada:"

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:486
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:486"
msgid "Argument rules:"
msgstr "Reglas de argumentos:"

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:488
msgid "`ptool.run(cmdline)`: `cmdline` is split using shell-style (`shlex`) rules. The first item is treated as the command and the rest as arguments."
msgstr "`ptool.run(cmdline)`: `cmdline` se divide usando reglas estilo shell (`shlex`). El primer elemento se trata como comando y el resto como argumentos."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:490
msgid "`ptool.run(cmd, argsline)`: `cmd` is used directly as the command, and `argsline` is split into an argument list using shell-style (`shlex`) rules."
msgstr "`ptool.run(cmd, argsline)`: `cmd` se usa directamente como comando y `argsline` se divide en una lista de argumentos con reglas estilo shell (`shlex`)."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:492
msgid "`ptool.run(cmd, args)`: `cmd` is a string and `args` is an array of strings."
msgstr "`ptool.run(cmd, args)`: `cmd` es una cadena y `args` es un arreglo de cadenas."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:493
msgid "`ptool.run(cmdline, options)`: `options` overrides settings for this invocation, such as `echo`."
msgstr "`ptool.run(cmdline, options)`: `options` sobrescribe la configuración de esta invocación, como `echo`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:495
msgid "`ptool.run(cmd, args, options)`: `args` can be either a string or an array of strings, and `options` overrides settings for this invocation, such as `echo`."
msgstr "`ptool.run(cmd, args, options)`: `args` puede ser una cadena o un arreglo de cadenas, y `options` sobrescribe la configuración de esta invocación, como `echo`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:497
msgid "`ptool.run(options)`: `options` is a table."
msgstr "`ptool.run(options)`: `options` es una tabla."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:498
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:498"
msgid "When the second argument is a table: if it is an array (consecutive integer keys `1..n`), it is treated as `args`; otherwise it is treated as `options`."
msgstr "Cuando el segundo argumento es una tabla: si es un arreglo (claves enteras consecutivas `1..n`), se trata como `args`; en caso contrario se trata como `options`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:501
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:501"
msgid "Return value rules:"
msgstr "Reglas del valor devuelto:"

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:503
msgid "A table is always returned with the following fields:"
msgstr "Siempre se devuelve una tabla con los siguientes campos:"

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:503
msgid "`ok` (boolean): Whether the exit code is `0`."
msgstr "`ok` (boolean): Si el código de salida es `0`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:503
msgid "`code` (integer|nil): The process exit code. If the process was terminated by a signal, this is `nil`."
msgstr "`code` (integer|nil): El código de salida del proceso. Si el proceso fue terminado por una señal, esto es `nil`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:503
msgid "`cmd` (string): Command name used for the execution."
msgstr "`cmd` (string): Nombre del comando usado para la ejecución."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:503
msgid "`cwd` (string): Effective working directory used for the execution."
msgstr "`cwd` (string): Directorio de trabajo efectivo usado para la ejecución."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:503
msgid "`stdout` (string, optional): Present when `stdout = \"capture\"`."
msgstr "`stdout` (string, opcional): Presente cuando `stdout = \"capture\"`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:503
msgid "`stderr` (string, optional): Present when `stderr = \"capture\"`."
msgstr "`stderr` (string, opcional): Presente cuando `stderr = \"capture\"`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:503
msgid "`assert_ok(self)` (function): Raises a structured error when `ok = false`. The error kind is `command_failed`, and the error may include `cmd`, `status`, `stderr`, and `cwd`."
msgstr "`assert_ok(self)` (function): Produce un error estructurado cuando `ok = false`. El tipo de error es `command_failed` y puede incluir `cmd`, `status`, `stderr` y `cwd`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:514
msgid "The default value of `check` comes from `ptool.config({ run = { check = ... } })`. If not configured, it defaults to `false`. When `check = false`, callers can inspect `ok` themselves or call `res:assert_ok()`."
msgstr "El valor por defecto de `check` proviene de `ptool.config({ run = { check = ... } })`. Si no se configura, el valor por defecto es `false`. Cuando `check = false`, quien llama puede inspeccionar `ok` por su cuenta o llamar a `res:assert_ok()`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:517
msgid "When both `check = true` and `retry = true`, `ptool.run` asks whether the failed command should be retried before raising the final error."
msgstr "Cuando `check = true` y `retry = true`, `ptool.run` pregunta si debe reintentarse el comando fallido antes de producir el error final."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:519
msgid "When `check = true`, `ptool.run` raises the same structured `command_failed` error that `res:assert_ok()` raises. Use `ptool.try(...)` if you want to catch and inspect it from Lua."
msgstr "Cuando `check = true`, `ptool.run` produce el mismo error estructurado `command_failed` que `res:assert_ok()`. Usa `ptool.try(...)` si quieres capturarlo e inspeccionarlo desde Lua."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:523
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:523"
msgid "Example:"
msgstr "Ejemplo:"

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:544
msgid "`ptool.run(options)` is also supported, where `options` is a table with the following fields:"
msgstr "También se admite `ptool.run(options)`, donde `options` es una tabla con los siguientes campos:"

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:547
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:547"
msgid "`cmd` (string, required): The command name or executable path."
msgstr "`cmd` (string, obligatorio): El nombre del comando o la ruta del ejecutable."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:548
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:548"
msgid "`args` (string[], optional): The argument list."
msgstr "`args` (string[], opcional): La lista de argumentos."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:549
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:549"
msgid "`cwd` (string, optional): The child process working directory."
msgstr "`cwd` (string, opcional): El directorio de trabajo del proceso hijo."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:550
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:550"
msgid "`env` (table, optional): Additional environment variables, where keys are variable names and values are variable values."
msgstr "`env` (table, opcional): Variables de entorno adicionales, donde claves y valores son nombres y valores de variable."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:552
msgid "`stdin` (string, optional): String sent to the child process stdin. When this is omitted, the child process inherits the current process stdin."
msgstr "`stdin` (cadena, opcional): cadena enviada a la entrada estándar del proceso secundario. Cuando se omite, el proceso hijo hereda la entrada estándar del proceso actual."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:554
msgid "`trim` (boolean, optional): Whether to trim leading and trailing whitespace from captured `stdout` and captured `stderr` before returning them. This only affects streams set to `\"capture\"`. Defaults to `false`."
msgstr "`trim` (booleano, opcional): si se deben recortar los espacios en blanco iniciales y finales de `stdout` y `stderr` capturados antes de devolverlos. Esto solo afecta a las transmisiones configuradas en `\"capture\"`. El valor predeterminado es `false`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:557
msgid "`echo` (boolean, optional): Whether to echo command information for this execution. If omitted, the value from `ptool.config({ run = { echo = ... } })` is used; if that is also unset, the default is `true`."
msgstr "`echo` (boolean, opcional): Si debe imprimirse información del comando para esta ejecución. Si se omite, se usa el valor de `ptool.config({ run = { echo = ... } })`; si también falta, el valor por defecto es `true`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:560
msgid "`check` (boolean, optional): Whether to raise an error immediately when the exit code is not `0`. If omitted, the value from `ptool.config({ run = { check = ... } })` is used; if that is also unset, the default is `false`."
msgstr "`check` (boolean, opcional): Si debe producirse un error inmediatamente cuando el código de salida no es `0`. Si se omite, se usa el valor de `ptool.config({ run = { check = ... } })`; si también falta, el valor por defecto es `false`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:563
msgid "`confirm` (boolean, optional): Whether to ask the user for confirmation before execution. If omitted, the value from `ptool.config({ run = { confirm = ... } })` is used; if that is also unset, the default is `false`."
msgstr "`confirm` (boolean, opcional): Si debe pedirse confirmación al usuario antes de ejecutar. Si se omite, se usa el valor de `ptool.config({ run = { confirm = ... } })`; si también falta, el valor por defecto es `false`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:566
msgid "`retry` (boolean, optional): Whether to ask the user whether to retry after a failed execution when `check = true`. If omitted, the value from `ptool.config({ run = { retry = ... } })` is used; if that is also unset, the default is `false`."
msgstr "`retry` (boolean, opcional): Si debe preguntarse al usuario si quiere reintentar después de un fallo cuando `check = true`. Si se omite, se usa el valor de `ptool.config({ run = { retry = ... } })`; si también falta, el valor por defecto es `false`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:570
