msgid "ptool.exec"
msgstr "ptool.exec"

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:656
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:656"
msgid "`Unreleased` - Introduced."
msgstr "`Unreleased` - Introducido."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:658
msgid "`ptool.exec` replaces the current `ptool` process with an external command."
msgstr "`ptool.exec` reemplaza el proceso actual de `ptool` por un comando externo."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:660
msgid "It supports the same command argument call forms as `ptool.run`:"
msgstr "Admite las mismas formas de llamada de argumentos de comando que `ptool.run`:"

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:671
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:671"
msgid "Behavior:"
msgstr "Comportamiento:"

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:673
msgid "On success, `ptool.exec` does not return. The current `ptool` process is replaced by the target command."
msgstr "Si tiene éxito, `ptool.exec` no devuelve. El proceso actual de `ptool` es reemplazado por el comando de destino."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:675
msgid "Any Lua code after a successful `ptool.exec(...)` call does not run."
msgstr "No se ejecuta ningún código Lua después de una llamada exitosa a `ptool.exec(...)`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:676
msgid "In `ptool repl`, a successful `ptool.exec(...)` also replaces the REPL process."
msgstr "En `ptool repl`, una llamada exitosa a `ptool.exec(...)` también reemplaza el proceso del REPL."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:678
msgid "On Unix platforms, this uses true process replacement semantics."
msgstr "En plataformas Unix, esto usa semántica real de reemplazo de proceso."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:679
msgid "On non-Unix platforms, `ptool.exec` currently raises an `unsupported` error."
msgstr "En plataformas no Unix, `ptool.exec` actualmente produce un error `unsupported`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:681
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:681"
msgid "Argument rules:"
msgstr "Reglas de argumentos:"

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:683
msgid "`ptool.exec(cmdline)`: `cmdline` is split using shell-style (`shlex`) rules. The first item is treated as the command and the rest as arguments."
msgstr "`ptool.exec(cmdline)`: `cmdline` se divide usando reglas de estilo shell (`shlex`). El primer elemento se trata como comando y el resto como argumentos."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:685
msgid "`ptool.exec(cmd, argsline)`: `cmd` is used directly as the command, and `argsline` is split into an argument list using shell-style (`shlex`) rules."
msgstr "`ptool.exec(cmd, argsline)`: `cmd` se usa directamente como comando y `argsline` se divide en una lista de argumentos con reglas de estilo shell (`shlex`)."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:687
msgid "`ptool.exec(cmd, args)`: `cmd` is a string and `args` is an array of strings."
msgstr "`ptool.exec(cmd, args)`: `cmd` es una cadena y `args` es un arreglo de cadenas."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:688
msgid "`ptool.exec(cmdline, options)`: `options` overrides settings for this invocation, such as `echo`."
msgstr "`ptool.exec(cmdline, options)`: `options` sobrescribe la configuración de esta invocación, por ejemplo `echo`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:690
msgid "`ptool.exec(cmd, args, options)`: `args` can be either a string or an array of strings, and `options` overrides settings for this invocation, such as `confirm`."
msgstr "`ptool.exec(cmd, args, options)`: `args` puede ser una cadena o un arreglo de cadenas, y `options` sobrescribe la configuración de esta invocación, por ejemplo `confirm`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:693
msgid "`ptool.exec(options)`: `options` is a table."
msgstr "`ptool.exec(options)`: `options` es una tabla."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:694
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:694"
msgid "When the second argument is a table: if it is an array (consecutive integer keys `1..n`), it is treated as `args`; otherwise it is treated as `options`."
msgstr "Cuando el segundo argumento es una tabla: si es un arreglo (claves enteras consecutivas `1..n`), se trata como `args`; en caso contrario se trata como `options`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:697
msgid "`ptool.exec(options)` is also supported, where `options` is a table with the following fields:"
msgstr "También se admite `ptool.exec(options)`, donde `options` es una tabla con los siguientes campos:"

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:700
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:700"
msgid "`cmd` (string, required): The command name or executable path."
msgstr "`cmd` (string, obligatorio): El nombre del comando o la ruta del ejecutable."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:701
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:701"
msgid "`args` (string[], optional): The argument list."
msgstr "`args` (string[], opcional): La lista de argumentos."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:702
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:702"
msgid "`cwd` (string, optional): The child process working directory."
msgstr "`cwd` (string, opcional): El directorio de trabajo del proceso hijo."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:703
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:703"
msgid "`env` (table, optional): Additional environment variables, where keys are variable names and values are variable values."
msgstr "`env` (table, opcional): Variables de entorno adicionales, donde claves y valores son nombres y valores de variable."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:705
msgid "`echo` (boolean, optional): Whether to echo command information before replacement. If omitted, the value from `ptool.config({ run = { echo = ... } })` is used; if that is also unset, the default is `true`."
msgstr "`echo` (boolean, opcional): Si debe mostrarse información del comando antes del reemplazo. Si se omite, se usa el valor de `ptool.config({ run = { echo = ... } })`; si tampoco está definido, el valor predeterminado es `true`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:708
msgid "`confirm` (boolean, optional): Whether to ask the user for confirmation before replacement. If omitted, the value from `ptool.config({ run = { confirm = ... } })` is used; if that is also unset, the default is `false`."
msgstr "`confirm` (boolean, opcional): Si debe pedirse confirmación al usuario antes del reemplazo. Si se omite, se usa el valor de `ptool.config({ run = { confirm = ... } })`; si tampoco está definido, el valor predeterminado es `false`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:711
msgid "Unlike `ptool.run`, `ptool.exec` does not support `stdin`, `trim`, `stdout`, `stderr`, `check`, or `retry`."
msgstr "A diferencia de `ptool.run`, `ptool.exec` no admite `stdin`, `trim`, `stdout`, `stderr`, `check` ni `retry`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:713
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:713"
msgid "When `confirm = true`:"
msgstr "Cuando `confirm = true`:"

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:713
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:713"
msgid "If the user refuses the execution, an error is raised immediately."
msgstr "Si el usuario rechaza la ejecución, se produce un error de inmediato."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:713
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/worktrees/ptool/fresh-vale/ptool/website/docs/lua-api/core.md:713"
msgid "If the current environment is not interactive (no TTY), an error is raised immediately."
msgstr "Si el entorno actual no es interactivo (sin TTY), se produce un error de inmediato."

